just_use article_comments.go

# label: SPIKE (ANCHOR_COMMENTS stack)
# role: Gopher view — inline paragraph-anchored comments on articles

Small commenting system scoped to long-form markdown
articles (essays, wiki pages). Comments anchor to a
specific paragraph index, not a line or character range —
the granularity humans actually care about when reading
linearly.

## Storage: sibling JSON file

Each article at `foo.md` stores comments at
`foo.md.comments.json`. Shape:

```
{"comments": [
  {"para_index": 3, "author": "steve", "timestamp": "...", "text": "..."},
  ...
]}
```

No database, no schema migration. Deletion = `rm`. One
file per article; moves/renames should carry the sidecar
along.

## Routes

- `GET /gopher/article-comments?article=<path>` — returns
  the JSON for a given article path.
- `POST /gopher/article-comments` — form post with
  `article`, `para_index`, `author`, `text`; appends one
  comment and returns the updated list.

## Path resolution

`resolveArticlePath` takes `<repo>/<sub>` and refuses
anything that escapes a known repo root. Security-relevant
— this is the one spot where user input names a filesystem
path.

## Why per-paragraph, not per-line

Markdown paragraphs are a stable unit across reflow,
typography changes, and minor edits. A line anchor breaks
the moment the author rewraps. Paragraph indexes survive
edits as long as paragraph *order* is preserved.

## Pointers

- Part of: ANCHOR_COMMENTS stack
  (`project_anchor_comments_stack.md`).
- Imports: `angry-gopher/auth` for author attribution on
  POST.
- Consumer: the article-rendering view (essays, wiki) that
  injects inline comment widgets per paragraph.
